data.text:
Lake County Extends Financial Aid to Gary Police

(Crown Point - July 18, 2024) Lake County Government is providing more than $250,000 in funding to the City of Gary to help pay for badly needed equipment and improvements for the Gary Police Department.

Lake County reaches agreement on Police contract

(Crown Point - July 9, 2024) The Lake County Council Tuesday approved an agreement with the Fraternal Order of Police Union Chris Anton Lodge No. 125/Lake County Police Association Local 72 AFL/CIO resolving the ongoing contract negotiations for the Sheriff's Department.

July 9, 2024 - County Council honors Munster High School's Champion Speech and Debate Team

Munster High School's Speech and Debate Team was honored Tuesday, July 9, by the Lake County Council after the team captured its 14th consecutive state championship title and went on to earn its 10th national title in the past 12 years.

ANNUAL ACTION PLAN SUBSTANTIAL AMENDMENTS

The Lake County Community Economic Development Department (LCCEDD) is proposing to amend the Fiscal Year (FY) 2018, 2019, 2020, 2021, 2022, and 2023 Annual Action Plans (9-1-2018 to 8-31-2024) for use of HOME Investment Partnership Program funds (HOME).

Transparency in Coverage Act

The following link, https://www.cigna.com/legal/compliance/machine-readable-files, leads to the machine readable files that are made available in response to the federal Transparency in Coverage Rule and includes negotiated service rates and out-of-network allowed amounts between health plans and healthcare providers. The machine-readable files are formatted to allow researchers, regulators, and application developers to more easily access and analyze data.
